                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#26v #36v #45r #47v #118v" facs="029 039 047 050 121">Fols. 26v, 36v, 45r, 47v, 118v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#20v #77r" facs="023 079">Fols. 20v, 77r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    erasure markings are visible;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#14v #19r #20r #24v" facs="017 021 022 027">Fols. 14v, 19r, 20r, 24v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r #2v #3r #3v" facs="004 005 006">Fols. 1v, 2r, 2v, 3r, 3v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex (e.g. 1v, 2rv, 3rv) But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (2rv)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
